snippet: The 12-year-old amateur Ye Wocheng, the youngest player to compete on the European Tour, missed the cut at the China Open in Tianjin.
abstract: Ye Wocheng, 12-year-old amateur of China, youngest golfer to compete on European Tour, misses cut at China Open in Tianjin; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: The 12-year-old amateur Ye Wocheng, the youngest player to compete on the European Tour, missed the cut at the China Open in Tianjin.

headline.seo: Ye Wocheng Misses Cut at China Open
